2) Target the PR to develop branch.

@mxz96102 @raulchen  it seems to be working now!

I'm ok to merge this with the following change: can we place change the naming of the buttoms from "TRY NEW DASHBOARD" to "TRY EXPERIMENTAL DASHBOARD" and "BACK TO LEGACY" to "BACK TO EXISTING DASHBOARD"? I'd also like it if we could remove the "SUMMARY" page entirely as it's basically just a blank screen right now.

I have a bunch of other small feedback on how we can improve this dashboard before we ask for feedback from OSS users. I will file this under a github milestone in the couple of days.

Thanks @andrei-menzopol. 
I think it will help to define the data structures and their format more clearly. We can specify the different types and constants:

```c++
/**
 * Max buffer size (in bytes) for representing the EDCSA key-pair in DER format.
 *
 */
#define OT_CRYPTO_ECDSA_MAX_DER_SIZE 125

/**
 * This structure represents an ECDSA key pair (public and private keys).
 *
 * The key pair is stored using Distinguished Encoding Rules (DER) format (per RFC 5915).
 *
 */
typedef struct otPlatCryptoEcdsaKeyPair
{
    uint8_t mDerBytes[OT_CRYPTO_ECDSA_MAX_DER_SIZE];
    uint8_t mDerLength;
} otPlatCryptoEcdsaKeyPair;


#define OT_CRYPTO_ECDSA_PUBLIC_KEY_SIZE 64 // Should check if it is correct

/**
 * This struct represents a ECDSA public key.
 *
 * The public key is stored as a byte sequence representation of an uncompressed curve point (RFC 6605 - sec 4).
 *
 */
OT_TOOL_PACKED_BEGIN
struct otPlatCryptoEcdsaPublicKey
{
    uint8_t m8[OT_CRYPTO_ECDSA_PUBLIC_KEY_SIZE];
}
OT_TOOL_PACKED_END;

typedef struct otPlatCryptoEcdsaPublicKey otPlatCryptoEcdsaPublicKey;

/**
 * This struct represents an ECDSA signature.
 *
 * The signature is encoded as the concatenated binary representation of two MPIs `r` and `s` which are calculated
 * during signing (RFC 6605 - section 4).
 *
 */
OT_TOOL_PACKED_BEGIN
struct otPlatCryptoEcdsaSignature
{
    uint8_t m8[...] (TODO)
};
```

And then we can define the platform APIs to mirror public methods of different `Ecdsa` classes:

```c++
otError otPlatCryptoEcdsaGenerateKey(otPlatCryptoEcdsaKeyPair *aKeyPair);

otError otPlatCryptoEcdsaGePublicKey(const otPlatCryptoEcdsaKeyPair *aKeyPair, otPlatCryptoEcdsaPublicKey *aPublicKey);

otError otPlatCryptoEcdsaSign(const otPlatCryptoEcdsaKeyPair *aKeyPair, 
                              const otCryptoSha256Hash *      aHash, 
                              otPlatCryptoEcdsaSignature *    aSignature);

otError otPlatCryptoEcdsaVerify(const otPlatCryptoEcdsaPublicKey *aPublicKey,
                                const otCryptoSha256Hash *      aHash,
                                const otPlatCryptoEcdsaSignature *    aSignature);
```

> I don't really see the use case where you would like to generate a categorical dataset with more than 256 categories.

@strandgren The second we say it isn't going to be needed is when people needed it. I know of an algorithm developer who did something like 64-128 for categories and then 255-65535 as "floating point" values to act like a gradient for a particular category.

> But in case of providing float I would tend to agree with @gerritholl that one could the output of a CategoricalDataCompositor to be int.

@strandgren I think there is a word or two missing here. You agree it should only be ints?

@gerritholl This looks pretty good to me. I had some suggestions to maybe clear things up and offer additional defaults. Let me know what you think.

@jtook this is not a `feat` it is at maximum a `fix` because you included changes at the level of the `correlation.py` file. 

As examples are out of the package they should not be considered for version increment of the package. Can you please change the PR message in accordance?
Also, can you please confirm the license of the dataset used? 

@aquemy as this is for the feature folder and not for the use-cases folder, I'll ask to have this changed to a python file. The change is minor and it eases the consumption of the code to generate automated documentation, as we have in other examples.

Notebooks should be used for examples such as `usaairquality` or `employees-chicago`.
